inn1.comm: beaten, gets it to move away after landing on a good length outside off, Butt pokes at it and is lucky not to get an outside edge
short and down the leg side, was trying to work it fine, didn't make contact but earns a wide
bowls it on a good length on middle at 138 kmph, gets on the back foot and knocks it back down on the pitch
bowled it full on the off, rocked forward and guided it with an open face towards point
short and wide, that's Butt's zone, slashes it hard over point to the boundary wide of third man
targeting middle and leg, gets forward and presents the full face while pushing it to mid-on
hurls it on a good length outside off, moves away and he shoulders arms to leave it be
short of a length outside off, cut away towards point
shortish on middle and off, rocks back and knocks it down back to the bowler
Siddle hurls it at 141.4 kmph, drives it confidently down the ground but straight to mid-on
full on middle and leg, deals with it well, driving it between mid-on and midwicket for three runs
lands on a good length on leg stump, tries to clip it to the fine-leg boundary but it ends up brushing his pads
lands on a good length on the off, gets front and across and dabs it into the leg side
short of a good length outside off and darting away, Kamran guides it down to third man for a single
good bounce and movement to back it up, surprised Butt there as he tried to defend that off the back foot, was beaten but Bollinger has overstepped and concedes a freehit
full on the off stump, Butt had made room and he ends up steering it between point and cover to the ropes, nicely done
short of a good length outside off, nipping away and he leaves it be
gets forward and defends it with a full face back to the bowler
confident start, this, full outside off, a juicy-half volley that he dispatches wide of mid-off for his third boundary
bowls it on a good length outside off, gets forward and eases it wide of cover, it's well fielded by Clarke who dives to his right
targeting the good length again, driven firmly but straight to mid-off
short and wide, cut away to third man for a single
short of a good length on the off, rocks back to tap it towards cover
edged and four, overpitched and it draws him into playing the drive, gets a thick outside edge wide of second slip to beat third man to the ropes
slightly short on the off, gets on the back foot and plays it towards point
short and down the leg side, called a wide
lands it on a good length outside off, driven hard through the covers, Hussey gives chase and hauls it back in but the batsmen have taken three by then
short of a length just a fraction outside off, holds its line and he lets it be
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and taps it towards point
well left in the end, lands on a good length outside off and nips back in but he watches it closely and allows it through
pushed it fuller, just outside off, stretches forward and pushes it to mid-off
bowls it on the stumps this time, just on middle and off, meets it respectfully with a full face while playing it back to the bowler
ooh, almost had him, short and wide and he slashed at it really hard, flew off the outside edge over the outstretched hands of Cameron White at second slip, nice try but he couldn't get to it
shortish on the off, punched off the back foot towards point
bowled it full on the off, dug it out towards cover off the front foot
short again and he is well in control of this one, had ample time to rock back and make room and swat it between cover and point for a boundary

quicker, bowled at 147 kmph, and fuller but he is in a confident mood, drives it on the up between cover and mid-off for three more, good teamwork by Hussey and Clarke who give chase and haul it back in
short of a good length on leg stump, tries to whip it square, is struck high on the pads
punched it off the front foot wide of mid-off for a single
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and taps it towards point
hurls it short on the off, stands tall and defends it in front of cover
bowls it on a good length outside off, pushed towards cover
was drawn forward with a fuller delivery, lunged at it and ended up playing it uppishly in the direction of cover
short and wide, slashes hard, was there to hit but missed out
created a chance with his first delivery, pushed it full outside off, sliced it just wide of a diving point, Ponting couldn't get to it, just the single
short of a length outside off, shoulders arms to leave it to the keeper
short again, turned away into the leg side in front of square leg for a single
short and wide, they've bowled quite a few of those today, cut away fiercely through point, deserved to go for four
bowls it from slightly wide of the crease, lands it on a good length and gets it to nip away as he plays forward, just escapes the outside edge
slightly short on the off, taps it just in front of cover
loosener to start with, short of a good length on middle, defended off the back foot towards cover
attacking stand, this, a length delivery on middle and leg, makes room and smashes it over the bowler's head for a boundary
short of a length on the off, defended off the back foot to the bowler
hurled it short on middle, went after it, tried to pull it hard but found midwicket
pushed it full on middle and off, defended solidly towards mid-off
pushed it off the front foot towards mid-off
short of a good length on the off, dabs it in front of point
hurls it full on the off, square-driven straight to point
angling it in towards middle, defended into the off side
nice, clean strike, not quite a length delivery but he backed himself there, lofted him over mid-off, came off the middle and earned four
a little wider this time and was made to reach for it, got a thick outside edge to third man for a single
short of a length outside off, allows it through to the keeper
short of a length outside off, cut away down to third man for a single
bouncer, the first of the day, ducks under it comfortably
short of a length on middle, fends it away into the leg side
drops it in front of extra cover and calls for a single but is wisely sent back
short of a length outside off, turning in sharply, makes room to cut it down to point
bends low and paddles it down towards fine leg for a single
slightly short on middle, punched down towards mid-on
short of a length and turning in, tries to chop it into the off side, gets an inside edge just wide of the leg stump
pushed away wide of square leg for a single
quicker through the air from round the wicket, nudges it down behind square towards fine leg for an easy couple
bowls it on a good length on the off, defended towards cover from the crease

short of a length outside off, slashed wide of slip and third man for a single, Hauritz returns an accurate throw from the deep and throws down the stumps at the striker's end, Butt was wise to refuse the second
banged in short on middle, a bouncer but a harmless one, ducks under
short of a length outside off, punched off the back foot towards third man for a single, Butt decides against the second though it was probably worth going for it

Kamran goes, a needless shot under the circumstances, a slower delivery, a legcutter bowled just outside off, tries to smash him over the in-field on the off side but failed to pick the change in pace and ended up skying it, Clarke and Ponting get underneath it but the deputy calls first and holds on to a well-judged catch
bowls it on a good length outside off and gets it to move away, leaves it alone
Butt, though, appears unflustered, slightly short and he slaps it on bended knee towards deep square leg for a couple
quicker through the air, bowled short outside off, cut away wide of deep point, there was a second in there but they opt against it
Younis off the mark, gets outside the line and tickles it behind square for a single
short of a length on the off, taps it in front of cover
shortish outside off, swats it wide of cover for an easy single
lands on a good length on the off, drops it in front of cover, thinks of a single but it's not there
nicely played, did so really late, short of a good length and he opened the face at just the right time to guide it wide of third man for a couple, McKay does well sliding to his left
hurled it short outside off and goes for the favoured cut, gets a thick edge that flies over Haddin to the ropes
short of a good length on the off, gets an inside edge onto his pad as he tries to play t into the off side
shortish on middle and leg, worked away behind square for a single
bowled it short on the off, rocks back and knocks it down on the pitch
gave it a good crack, Siddle comes back to bowl it on a length outside off, Butt made room and sliced it over point to the boundary
edged and four! Bowls it on a good length, draws him forward and the movement away produces the outside edge, Cameron White dives valiantly to his left at slip but can't get to it, four more
no respite for Siddle here, Butt's targeting him, short on middle and he was quick to seize the length, hammering it past midwicket for his third consecutive four
beaten this time, slightly short on the off and tries to nudge it into the off side, doesn't make contact
short of a length on middle, pushed into the off side
shortish on middle, worked away into the leg side
short of a length outside off stump, Younis stays back and punches the ball behind point
Butt gets a touch squared up and the outside edge goes towards third man, safely though
the bouncer at 143.7 kmh, Younis ducks under it
good length delivery on off stump, Younis defends towards the bowler, that ball hit the shoulder of the bat and then as it came down it hit the blade as well
fuller length outside off stump, Younis strides forward and plays the ball towards cover
good length outside off, Younis stays in his crease and plays towards cover again
good length ball on off stump, Butt drops the ball towards point and wants the single to reach his half-century, Younis sends him back
played Butt! He gets to fifty by dabbing the ball towards third man, he's picked up his strike-rate as well, Pakistan need him to go all the way
Younis tries to block a good length ball but gets an inside edge on to the pad
off the back foot but straight to point, Younis isn't finding timing or placement regularly yet
good length and straight, Younis defends towards the bowler
beaten! Siddle pitches the ball short of a length outside off, Younis hangs his bat out limply ...
Butt uses the room created by McKay's angle across them to guide the ball to third man
unconvincing but Younis will get a single, he stayed back in his crease and pushed away from his body to play the ball to third man
McKay appeals but that pitched outside leg stump, Butt tried to flick but missed
Butt tries to dab the ball to third man again but the fielder at slip is a bit wider and he dives to his left to field the ball
Butt plays this one to point, there's a been a sudden lull in the scoring
Butt drops the ball on the off side but there's no quick single available
quickish ball on off and middle, Younis leans forward to play it
Butt skips down the pitch, he doesn't get near the bounce of the ball but manages to loft it inside out over extra cover, poor running, they should have got three
Butt sweeps and plays it fine on the leg side
Younis tries to sweep but misses it
played off the front foot towards long on
Butt sweeps, and connects, gets a single to deep square leg
slapped! Butt makes room and comes down the track, he swings his bat hard and launches the ball over extra cover
this time the ball is closer to him and he dabs it towards the fielder at slip, he was looking for third man
shot! Butt makes room again and, though the length is shorter, Butt flat-bats the ball high over mid off for a one-bounce four
another one! Poor line on leg stump and Butt plays a deft leg glance to the fine-leg boundary, he's taken the pressure off now
short of a length outside off stump, Butt guides the ball towards third man
full ball outside off, Younis drives through cover to retain strike
Younis gets down on one knee to sweep but doesn't connect properly, he gets a top edge towards short fine leg
Hauritz goes round the wicket and bowls a flat one on off, Butt defends on the off side
Butt charges the spinner and lofts the ball high over mid-on, he hasn't hit it well enough to reach the boundary though
played off the back foot through cover point for a single
played off the pads through square leg for a single
bowled quicker through the air on off stump, defended on the back foot
short of a length and wide outside off stump, Butt has a really hard slash at it but doesn't connect

Bollinger's done it! Another shortish ball but it wasn't short enough to pull, Butt went for it anyway and top-edged it, Haddin took a second or two to pick up where the ball was going, he then turned around, ran back a few paces and held on to the catch
defended on the back foot towards the bowler
dabbed off the front foot towards the off side
short ball that gets up into Younis ribs, he plays an awkward mis-timed pull to square leg
short of a length into Yousuf's body, he fends the ball down on the leg side
Hauritz drifts down leg side and that's a wide, Younis tried to work it behind square but couldn't reach it
driven down the ground towards long on
played on the leg side
Yousuf works the ball towards midwicket
this time he dabs it late and places it fine to get the single
Younis moves forward to try and play the ball towards long on, Ponting intercepts from midwicket
defended on the front foot
full length on off stump, driven firmly off the front foot for a single to mid-off
nicely square driven, Younis reaches out for the ball outside off and places it past the fielder at point
tight line and length on off stump, Yousuf stays in his crease and defends

bowled him!! Superb short ball from Bollinger does for Yousuf. Bollinger got the ball to rise sharply from just short of a length, Yousuf jumped up to defend it, he got bat to ball but the ball bounced behind him and he watched it bounce on to the top of the stumps and dislodge the bails, I wonder why he didn't attempt to swat it away with the bat, he had loads of time to hit the ball away
144 kmh, defended on the off side from the crease
snorter, absolute snorter! Bollinger digs in another short one and has Akmal trying to get out of the way in a tearing hurry
played off the back foot behind square on the off side
the length is a bit short and Akmal goes back to cut to deep point
Akmal pushes forward tentatively to a flighted delivery and gets an edge past Clarke at first slip
Akmal rocks back to pull one that isn't too short but manages to hit it past midwicket
a touch shorter outside off and Akmal cuts the ball really hard behind point, Akmal's dealing in twos here
shot! Risky though! Akmal played the latest of dabs, virtually taking the ball out of Haddin's gloves, and placing it so fine that third man had zero chance of stopping that
played off the back foot towards the leg side, Younis seemed to want a run! Akmal sent him back
short ball outside off stump, Younis stays in his crease and hits the ball over cover point
Akmal moves a touch towards the off side, McKay responds with a bouncer and Akmal has to let it go
another short ball but this time it's down leg side and that's a wide
short of a length on off stump, Akmal gets behind the line and blocks
oh that's wide outside off stump and Akmal chases it without moving his feet and gets beaten
Akmal plays the ball towards the vacant space at midwicket and calls for the single, McKay has to run across to field
he's played that late cut again, the ball was nearly past him when he brought the bat down to place it super fine, the fielder gave chase but couldn't stop it
cut off the back foot to deep point
Younis has broken free! He gets down on one knee and slog-sweeps the ball from outside off stump towards the gap on the deep midwicket boundary
played back to the bowler on the front foot
nudged off the pads towards the leg side
not that short, not that short at all, but Akmal goes right back and heaves the ball over midwicket, he's hit it in the gap as well, there's always something happening when he faces up to Hauritz!
Younis plays the ball towards third man for a single
short ball outside off stump, Younis rides the bounce and guides the ball towards third man
defended from the crease towards the off side
edged but it falls short! Younis pushes away from his body at a good length ball and gets a thick outside edge, the ball begins to die as it reaches Ponting, he dives forward but it still falls short
what happened there! Younis tried to pull a short ball, the bat turned in his hand and he got no timing at all, the ball lobbed in the air and fell well short of mid-off
driven off the front foot towards mid off
full ball, nearly a yorker, Akmal defends but not very well
short of a length just outside off stump, defended on the back foot
Akmal stays in his crease and plays a good length delivery on the off side
the slower yorker, 122.5kmh, Akmal was beaten, well and truly, luckily for him the line was just outside off
short of a length and very close to the body, Akmal tried to cut but has no room whatsoever
terrific over from Siddle, a maiden, the last ball is a full one and Akmal plays it from his crease to mid off
good length ball outside off stump, pushed towards cover for a single
edged and gone! Akmal has been troubled when the length is shorter and now he slashes at a short and wide one from McKay and Haddin takes an easy catch
good length on off stump, defended on the off side
fuller length outside off, Malik drives to mid-off
beaten! McKay pitches around off and gets the ball to shape away from Malik ever so slightly, opening him up
short and wide outside off stump, Malik barely moves his feet but he gives the ball a fearful crack and sends it racing to the backward point boundary
driven off the front foot towards long off
Malik strides forward and defends
played off the pads behind square, they run a single
Younis backs away and plays the ball from his stumps towards point
the paddle sweep and Younis has placed this fine
a full toss on off stump, Malik drives to long off
driven off the front foot back to the bowler
wide ball, Malik went for the cut and missed, he lost balance and fell in his crease
driven down the ground for one

Younis tries to blast one down the ground but misses, Haddin whips off the bails, the third umpire is called for ... this is super close, his foot was outside the line but it moves back towards it as Haddin breaks the bails, it's really really close, it might be on the line, a fraction of a fraction might be behind it ... Paul Reiffel is the third umpire ... and he's given Younis the benefit of the slimmest of doubts
Younis stays in his crease and dabs the ball late towards third man
driven off the front foot towards the bowler, Hussey dives and fields
played off the back foot towards mid off
played to midwicket
Malik gets down on one knee and sweeps towards deep backward square leg
Malik reaches out for it and plays to cover
pulled towards deep backward square leg for a single
defended back to the bowler
full ball on off stump, driven off the front foot to point where Clarke fields
pushed off the front foot to mid off
full ball outside off stump, Malik brings his bat down and chops it past point
Malik drives a length delivery through the gap at cover
good length ball outside off, driven off the front foot through cover point
wide ball outside off stump, Younis reaches out for it and lofts over extra cover
low full toss on the off, driven firmly but straight to mid-off
short of a good length outside off, guided to point off the back foot
length delivery on the off, pushed through the line to mid-off for a single
short outside off, cut away down towards third man for a single
pushed it fuller on the off, driven back to the bowler who fumbles, allows a single and lets out a cry in frustration
more agony for Bollinger who slides one full outside off, goes at it hard, gets a thick outside edge and it races away to the third-man boundary
full outside off, driven wide of cover for a single into the deep
sliced away towards third man for a single
short of a good length on the off, drops it in front of cover and steals a single
short of a length outside off, goes for the cut but can't connect
bangs it short on middle, drops it off the back foot in front of cover
hurled it short on leg stump, moves well across to play it fine, misses, the umpre doesn't call it a wide
shortish on leg stump, tries to tickle it into the leg side, clips the pads and he gets the single
short of a length on the off, knocked down into the off side for a single
bowled it full on the off, Younis drives it towards mid-off, there's  no single on offer
pushed down the ground towards long-on for a single
worked away into the leg side through square leg
bowled it on a good length on the off, driven through the line back to the bowler
quick single taken, dropped it short on the off and scampered through for a run in front of Clarke at point
tight line, bowls it on a good length on the off, defended towards cover, they need to get a move-on now
bowled it short on the off, makes way and guides it uppishly towards third man who collects it on the bounce and keeps them down to a single
bowled it full outside off, comes down the track and tries to work it to  leg, ends up getting a leading edge wide of cover for a couple
short of a length outside off, chops it wide of point for a single
shortish on middle, punched off the back foot towards midwicket
gets it past a diving Ponting this time for a single to long-on
bowled it short outside off, makes room to cut it away down towards point for a single
went straight on, short outside off, opened the face to play it behind point this time for one more
Pakistan lose their fifth, similar dismissal to that of Umar Akmal, it's short and wide and he makes room to play a cut, gets a thick edge straight to Haddin
fullish on middle and leg, flicked away through square leg for a single
full outside off, a slower one, sliced away towards point
short one, nipping in, drops it off the back foot in front of point, there's no run on offer there
follows that up with a bouncer, ducks under it easily, a touch too high but not called a wide
short of a good length on middle, turned away behind square, just wide of fine leg, for a couple of runs
Afridi steps out of the track and smashes that towards long-on on the bounce
swept away towards deep square leg for a single
short of a length outside off, cracked from the crease towards deep point for a single
short on middle, pulled away to deep square leg for one more
into the stands, gave it a bit of air and he sensed a chance, charged down the track and dispatched it over long-on
short and wide, there to cut, makes room to do exactly that but is surprised by the bounce, misses
lands on a good length on middle, driven through the line to long-on for a single
banged in short on middle, a good timely bouncer, ducks under it
banged it short on middle, ducks under it again, the camera pans to the umpire who gives no signal
hurled it short on middle, shuffles and dabs it wide of midwicket and races for a single, Ponting picks and aims at the stumps at the non-striker's end but Afridi has made it
dropped, Younis gets a reprieve, short outside off, guided straight to third man where Hauritz, moving forward, spills it despite covering pretty good ground
and he strikes immediately, short on the off stump and Younis goes for the pull, sends it straight into the palms of Shaun Marsh running in from deep square leg, judged it well
slower one, ends up being a full toss and above waist height, paddles it to short fine, a no-ball's called
short of a length outside off, cut away hard behind point, the field is up and he finds the gap, four to the score
short of a good length on the off, dabs it into the leg side and sneaks a single
edged and gone, Aamer has edged it straight to Haddin, in the channel outside off and he simply pokes at it, gets a thin nick, tame dismissal
starts with a four, it's full outside off and he pushes at it, it works for it yields an outside edge to beat third man to the ropes
short of a good length outside off, guided to point off the front foot, no single there
that's bludgeoned into the stands, drops in a short delivery and he makes way to club it over deep midwicket, powerful strike and a spectator in the stands cannot hold on
four more, short again and he tries to pull it square this time, gets a top edge to beat Haddin's leap, just what Pakistan need
length delivery outside off, makes room and tries to cart it over cover, doesn't get enough bat on it but such is his strength that he manages to almost get it to the ropes, three more
bowled it full outside off, pushed it with an angled bat towards point
another dot ball, short of a good length and he wants to give Afridi the strike, trying to nudge it to third man but makes no contact
three in a row, fullish on the off, pushed off the front foot to cover, decides against the single, good comeback after the early treatment
slower one bowled on a good length on the off, shuffles across and turns it away wristily behind square leg for a couple
slower one bowled short on the off, makes room to dismiss him over mid-off, doesn't pick the slower one, misses
picks it this time, short down the leg side, shuffles and chips it over short fine leg to the fine-leg boundary
another one, slower ball but it's short and wide, makes room to play the cut, gets a thick outside edge over point and short third man for another boundary
poor McKay, good length on middle and off, makes room to smash him through cover, gets a thick outside edge again, well side of the keeper for four more

Afridi has turned it around in a matter of a few deliveries, shuffles across, it's full on leg stump and he tries to clip it fine, gets bat to it as well as pad and it races down the fine-leg boundary, the umpire calls it leg byes even but Pakistan will take it
bowled it short outside off, cut away down towards third man for a single
slower one bowled short on the off, mistimes a pull to midwicket
too wide and a full toss, Afridi makes room to crack it wide of point, was above the waist but it wasn't called, got a faint touch to it oxn the way to the keeper on the bounce
punished, full toss, a gift delivery under the circumstances, makes room and smashes it into the stands over long-on, flat hit

Watson gets him with a short one, banged it in on the off stump and he tried to clear deep midwicket with a pull but didn't have much on this one, Hussey was perfectly positioned and took it comfortably
full outside off, driven to cover
short of a length on the off, drops it in front of cover and steals a quick single, had White aim accurately at the non-striker's end, we would have had a wicket
short outside off, slapped straight to extra cover
yorker length on middle, digs it out wide of midwicket for a single
hurled it full outside off, cracked straight to extra cover
full and he only manages to squeeze it to point, good over
short of a length on middle, comes down the track to play it past midwicket, strikes the helmet on its way to Haddin
a desperate swing amid a thirst for runs at the death, is lucky to get away, he gets hardly anything on it and it lands safe in front of mid-on and mid-off
pushed into the off side towards cover for a single
low full toss on the off, drags it along the ground towards long-on for a single
bowled it short on middle, walks across to paddle it fine, misses, quite predictably
his eyes lit up as it landed on a length and he struck it fairly well too but straight down long-on's throat, didn't get the elevation he wanted, Watson's taken four, his best figures in ODIs
full toss on middle, played back to the bowler
hurls it full outside off, reaches to play it past point, straight through to the keeper
lands on a good length outside off, pushed off the front foot to extra cover

run out, Pakistan are bowled out, short on middle, goes for the pull, hits him on the arm and lobs up to slip, appeal for a caught behind turned down but they decide to go through with the run and Ponting scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end to find Asif short

inn2.comm: bowls it on a good length outside off and gets it to move away, Watson lets it be
short and wide and it's cut away hard wide of third man, Ajmal, moving to his right, fumbles and allows them to come back for the second
lands it on a good length on the off, defended on the pitch solidly
bowls it in the channel outside off, appears to hold its line, leaves it alone
lands on a good length on the off, gets forward and drops it in front of cover
tight line outside off, trying to tempt him to drive but Watson is restrained, leaving it alone
short of a length outside off, moving away and lets it go
slightly short again, in the corridor outside off, shoulders arms to that one
back of a length outside off, cut down towards third man for a single to get off the mark
fired it at 141.6 kmph on middle and leg, worked away down towards fine leg for a single
shortish on the off, gets back and taps it towards cover
hurls it on a good length on middle, gets across and knocks it down into the leg side
short of a length, cuts it away hard towards third man for a single
angling it down the pads and Marsh deals with it well, flicking it away wide of fine leg for Australia's first boundary
lands on a good length outside off and shoots away to beat the outside edge as he gets back to defend
shortish on leg stump, dabbed it into the leg side in front of midwicket
closes the face on that one to work it away behind square for a single
hurls it short outside off, chops it down towards third man for a single
bowled it short outside off, left it alone to the keeper
wayward delivery, bowled at 142 kmph way down he leg side and there was no way Kamran Akmal could have got to that one, five wides
excellent pace, 145 kmph and nips back in sharply, Watson reacts late but does well enough to keep that one away from his pads, chopping it behind point

done in for pace and bounce, what a snorter from Aamer, fired it on the off stump and nips back in sharply and catches the handle of the bat as he looks away and tries to fend it off, lobs straight to mid-on to give Pakistan the early breakthrough
ooh, that must hurt, Aamer's in a fiery mood here, short of a good length and nips back in, 143.8 kmph, struck him hard on the stomach
shortish on middle and leg again, moves across to work it away, strikes him high on the pad
short of a good length on the off, dropped it in front of point for a quick single
a touch too wide there, a driving length but out of the batsman's reach
short of a good length outside off, moving away, bowled at 138 kmph, leaves it be
slightly short on the off, defended off the back foot in front of cover

targeting middle and off, Ponting got a stride froward and tried to defend but the bat was a long way away and it struck him on the pads as it nipped back in, struck him in line, appeal for lbw turned down, replays suggest it would have just clipped the bails, enough doubt there
cut away past point wide of third man for a couple of runs
short of a length outside off, gets on the back foot and cracks it wide of point for two more into the deep
bowled it short on the off, rocks back and taps it towards cover
short of a length outside off, moving away and Marsh lets it be
bowled it short outside off, wide enough again for Marsh to let go
bowled at 141.9 kmph, excellent bounce and carry to the keeper as it beat the outside edge there, bowled it from wide of the crease and Marsh defended it inside the line
